<common-name datatype='string'>hicAB</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>When &lt;i&gt;hicAB&lt;/i&gt; mRNA is produced from hicAp2, only the &lt;/i&gt;hicB&lt;/i&gt; cistron is translated; that is, this mRNA produces only HicB but not the HicA protein. This happens because this transcript starts just 1 base upstream of the SD sequence of &lt;i&gt;hicA&lt;/i&gt; [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/28266056&quot;&gt;Turnbull17&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
